<br>
I think the best way to encourage/enforce the fact that the new server is to be used for RP would be to implement this.<br>
<br>
If you turn on your roleplay flag, you know the one that is used to hide from SoW/Rez/Clarity/(random buff inserted here) beggars, yet not hide your guild?<br>
<br>
Well, what if turning on that RP flag prevented you from seeing and responding to any OOC messages and auctions?<br>
<br>
I think that would discourage non-rpers and and greif players.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts, critisms welcome.<br>
<br>
*edit* further refining the idea<br>
<br>
Anon mode of course would work as normal.<br>
<br>
A common complaint among RPers is that they can't RP with their friends because their friends are<br>
<br>
a) trapped in battle spam<br>
b) trapped in auction spam<br>
<br>
So, a /who all friends,  would show anon but a guild name,  you would know that person is in RP mode and has the time to RP with you.<br>
<br>
You could effectively tell from a distance who wants to RP and who does not at that moment.  Not everyone can RP 100% of their online time.  It is hard to do, for example, on a dragon raid or while practicing smithing and the like.<br>
<br>
Once again, any discussion, critism, welcome.<br>
